  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provision of Protection, GBV, Site Management and ES/NFI Support for Internally Displaced Persons (IDPs) in Tigray Region</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this project is to provide essential lifesaving Protection, GBV, Site Management, and Emergency SHELTER/Non-Food Items  Support for Internally Displaced Persons (IDPs) in Tigray Region. This UNHCR project will provide i)Rehabilitation and upgrading IDP sites and collective centers, ii)Providing access to protection and basic services to improve living conditions for all IDPs, including Persons With Specific Needs (PSN), GBV survivors, youth, and adolescents through material and psycho-social support iii)Undertake protection monitoring/counseling and iv) Provide IDPs with shelter kits and household core relief items and Cash for rent  targeting for vulnerable IDPs living in the urban, peri-urban and rural set up where rental facilities are available and accessible to 271,696  people, including 90,190  women, 83,690  men, 75,440  children, and 12,325  persons with disabilities</narrative>
  </description>
